8.4.3 Permission Boundaries
Immutable Runtime Rules
Cannot be changed at runtime:
• Ledger append-only rule
• Rule A enforcement (Capture → Action gating)
• Rule B enforcement (ManualOnly → Enabled gating)
• CCO immutability post-write
• Connector downgrade thresholds

Time-Boxed Override Rules
Overrides must include:
• scope
• reason_code
• actor_id
• region_id
• expires_at
• max_duration
Maximum durations:
• Feature override: 12 hours
• Threshold override: 4 hours
• Protective mode override: 2 hours
No override may exceed 12 hours.

Region-Scoped Rules
• Overrides must include region_id
• Cross-region overrides prohibited
• Failover logging must replicate ledger entries

Feature-Scoped Rules
• Feature flags cannot bypass enforcement rules
• Disabled feature cannot mutate core objects
• Auto-suppressed features cannot be manually enabled without QA validation

AI Cap Rules
When AI capacity exceeds defined cap:
• Enter throttle mode
• Reduce summarization depth
• Block non-essential batch jobs
• Emit ai_cap_exhausted event
AI throttling must never:
• Block evidence upload
• Block incident capture
• Block ledger writes

AI throttling is triggered by policy (latency + queue depth), not a fixed percent

“Two-layer summary model” behavior:

●Immediate minimal summary

●Deferred full analysis

Guarantees: throttling never blocks evidence capture, incident capture, trip creation


Rate Limit Rules
• Per-IP rate limit enforced
• Per-account mutation rate limit enforced
• Burst protection triggers protective_mode_entered

Connector State Rules
Connector downgrade governed by 12.5 .
Connector cannot be re-enabled unless:
• QA smoke test passed
• Downgrade metrics cleared
• Re-enable logged

Retention Modification Rules
Retention policy changes require:
• Founder laptop
• Step-up
• Justification field
• 24-hour delayed activation
Cannot retroactively reduce retention for existing records.

Crisis Enrollment Rules
Crisis policy change must:
• Be region-scoped
• Include duration
• Include financial impact projection
• Emit crisis_policy_changed

Never Silent Changes
The following cannot change silently:
• Threshold values
• Feature states
• Connector states
• Protective mode
• Retention policies
• Override state
• Region load classification
All must emit structured events.

