8.4.5 Immutable Action Ledger
Properties:
• Append-only
• No UPDATE
• No DELETE
• Write-once rows
Write Failure Behavior:
If ledger write fails:
• Block structural action
• Emit ledger_write_failure
• Enter Protective Mode
Read Access:
• Founder: full
• Support: filtered
• Traveler: limited to own events
Export Rules:
• Export generates ledger_exported event
• Redaction profile required
• Identity-bound export authorization required (see 8.7.13–8.7.16), including minor constraints
Evidence File Retention Policy
• Active dispute: retain until dispute closed + 12 months
 • Paid subscriber: retain up to 3–5 years (plan-configurable)
 • Non-subscriber: retain 12–24 months
 • If no dispute and no active subscription, file binaries may be purged per retention schedule
Purging file binaries does not delete ledger records of their existence.
Ledger entries must permanently record:
 • evidence_file_uploaded
 • evidence_file_purged
 • retention_policy_applied
Retention policy changes must emit:
 • retention_policy_modified

Pre-Purge Notification Requirement (B)
Before automatic purge of evidence file binaries:
• User must receive a single notification 30 days prior to purge
 • Notification must be delivered in-app
 • Email may be sent only if already configured (no additional delivery infrastructure required)
 • Notification must include:
●Number of files affected

●Scheduled purge date

●Option to download files

If user takes no action within the 30-day window, purge proceeds automatically.
Required Event:
 • evidence_purge_notice_sent
“Failure to open or acknowledge the notification does not prevent purge execution.”

Manual Deletion (C)
Users may manually delete evidence files at any time.
Manual deletion must:
 • Require explicit confirmation
 • Not delete ledger record of existence
 • Emit event: evidence_file_deleted_by_user
Manual deletion cannot bypass:
 • Active dispute retention
 • Legal hold flags
If deletion attempt is blocked due to dispute or legal hold:
 • Emit event: evidence_deletion_blocked

Legal Hold / Dispute Override
If evidence is subject to:
 • Active dispute
 • Regulatory inquiry
 • Legal hold
Automatic purge must be suspended.
Suspension must emit:
 • evidence_retention_extended
Suspension expiration must emit:
 • evidence_retention_restored

Cold Storage Tier
Evidence files older than 36 months may be moved to lower-cost storage tiers.
Movement to cold storage must:
 • Preserve immutability
 • Preserve retrieval capability
 • Emit event: evidence_moved_to_cold_storage
Cold storage retrieval must emit:
 • evidence_retrieved_from_cold_storage

Retention modifications must emit:
 • retention_policy_modified
Cross-Region Persistence:
• Write replicated to secondary region
• Async replication must complete < 5 seconds
• If replication fails → protective_mode_entered
Tamper Detection:
• Each row includes hash(previous_hash + payload)
• Daily checksum verification
• checksum_mismatch triggers protective_mode_entered
Cross-Region Cryptographic Anchoring (Triangulated, 15-Minute Checkpoints)
Checkpoint Cadence
 System must create a ledger checkpoint every 15 minutes per region.
Checkpoint Artifact
 Each checkpoint must include:
 • checkpoint_id
 • region_id
 • checkpoint_window_start_utc
 • checkpoint_window_end_utc
 • ledger_last_event_id
 • ledger_chain_hash_or_merkle_root
 • event_count_in_window
 • created_at_utc
Triangulated Anchoring Requirement
 Each region must write each checkpoint anchor into two other regions.
 Anchors are append-only records.
 Anchors must be verifiable by recomputing the checkpoint hash for the same time window.
Anchoring Failure Behavior
 If anchoring to one target region fails, the system continues anchoring to the second target.
 If anchoring to both targets fails, local ledger writes continue.
 Structural governance actions remain subject to Logging Failure Posture in 8.4.7.
Anchoring Events (required)
 • ledger_checkpoint_created
 • ledger_checkpoint_anchored
 • ledger_anchor_write_failed
 • ledger_anchor_verification_failed
 • ledger_anchor_verification_restored


