8.4.7 Logging Failure Posture
If logging pipeline stalls:
• Allow read operations
• Block structural mutations
• Display non-alarmist banner (Founder domain)
If ledger storage unreachable:
• Block feature flag changes
• Block overrides
• Allow incident capture
• Allow evidence upload (region staging queue only)
Queue Backpressure Posture (Explicit Queues)
Definitions
 • logging_event_queue: event emission pipeline queue (audit + observability events).
 • evidence_staging_queue: server-side staging queue for evidence chunk writes and finalize operations.
 • decision_compute_queue: background compute queue for non-essential processing (summaries, enrichment, analytics).
If logging_event_queue exceeds threshold
 • Block structural mutations (already enforced).
 • Continue incident capture and evidence upload only if evidence_staging_queue is healthy.
 • Emit: logging_queue_backpressure_detected.
 • Enter Protective Mode if logging_event_queue remains above threshold for more than 10 minutes.
If evidence_staging_queue exceeds threshold
 • Allow uploads.
 • Mark uploads as “Processing.”
 • Traveler may proceed to next steps.
 • Do not acknowledge “Complete” until staging finalize succeeds.
 • Emit: evidence_queue_backpressure_detected.
 • Enter Protective Mode if evidence_staging_queue remains above threshold for more than 15 minutes.
If decision_compute_queue exceeds threshold
 • Degrade non-essential work first (summarization depth reduction, analytics pause).
 • Do not block incident capture, trip creation, or evidence upload.
 • Emit: decision_queue_backpressure_detected.
 • Do not enter Protective Mode solely due to decision_compute_queue backlog.


• Enter Protective Mode
Never degrade:
• Evidence capture
• Incident capture
• Trip creation
●Evidence Upload Durability Posture
●Non-Negotiable
 • Uploads must not be silently dropped.
 • No full-file persistence on client devices.
●If logging pipeline stalls
 • Uploads may proceed if region-level staging writes succeed.
 • Structural actions remain blocked per 8.4.7 structural mutation rules.
●If cross-region anchoring is delayed or unavailable
 • Uploads proceed normally as long as region-level staging storage is healthy.
 • Traveler experience does not change unless the upload write-path is impacted.
●If region-level staging storage is degraded but recoverable
 • Allow uploads.
 • Mark uploads as “Processing.”
 • Traveler may proceed to next steps.
 • System must retry durability confirmation until completed.
●If region-level staging storage is unavailable
 • Do not persist files on client.
 • Do not acknowledge upload as complete.
 • Display: “Connection required to upload.”
 • Upload may resume automatically once secure connection is restored.
●Secure Connection Requirement
 • Upload submission requires active secure HTTPS connection.
 • No upload submission permitted over insecure or downgraded transport.
●Resumable Chunked Upload Requirement
 • Files must be divided into encrypted chunks in transit.
 • Each chunk must be durably written before acknowledging progress.
 • upload_session_id governs resume behavior.
 • Upload resumes from last confirmed chunk.
 • Upload cannot complete unless full chunk manifest is confirmed.
●Required Events
 • evidence_upload_accepted
 • evidence_upload_processing
 • evidence_upload_staged
 • evidence_upload_confirmed
 • evidence_upload_retry_scheduled



8.4.8 Emergency Escalation Policy
Triggers:
• ≥ 2 simultaneous region protective modes
• Ledger checksum mismatch
• Replication failure > 60 seconds
• Downgrade spike across 3+ airlines
Emergency Mode:
• Duration max 4 hours
• Structural overrides frozen
• Automation throttled
Mandatory Review:
• Founder review required within 24 hours
• Emergency exit must emit emergency_mode_exited
Emergency Mode must not widen permissions for external profiles (Guardian/Investor).
It may freeze or reduce actions — never expand them

8.4.9 Region-Aware Governance
Region-Scoped Overrides:
• Must include region_id
• No global override without explicit multi-region declaration
Cross-Region Isolation:
• No shared mutable threshold object
• Each region maintains independent load state
Region Failover Logging:
• Secondary region must accept writes
• On failover emit region_failover_triggered
New Region Expansion Protocol:
Requires:
• Baseline retention configuration
• Threshold default config
• Replication verified
• Smoke test pass

